abstract: The killing of Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi resonates in the presidential race.
snippet: The killing of Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi resonates in the presidential race.
lead_paragraph: While campaigning in Iowa, Mitt Romney was asked Thursday in a radio interview with KSCJ in Sioux City about the news that Col. Muammar el-Qaddafi, the former Libyan leader, had been killed in his hometown of Surt, and he praised the development

headline.main: Romney Credits Libyan People for Qaddafi's Demise
